main event: Two objects were observed together in formation, flashing lights that gave the appearance of blinking on and off. The objects were seen at an estimated altitude of 40-50,000 feet and disappeared in the distance after 1.5 minutes.
interesting points: The objects were tracked on radar, but the radar contact was negative.
The observer was not a relative, but an 'act observer'.
The sighting was relayed through Kansas City Air Traffic Control.
The observer stated the object gave the impression of being an unidentified object similar to other unidentified objects reported in the area.
The sighting was reported to various military commands, including the Air Defense Command and the Air Technical Intelligence Center.
sighted object: Two objects in formation with flashing lights
